section#grid
  h1.font_size--large-xxx Grid
  p the grid has 12 columns by default and 16px margin bottom space between 2 rows
  p The grid is defined using the class `grid_row` to define a row and `grid_column` to define a colum
  p simple example:
  .demo_grid
    +gridRow()
      each _, i in Array(12)
        +gridColumn()
          = i + 1
  p by default, the columns will break to next line if they dont fit the row
  .demo_grid
    +gridRow()
      each _, i in Array(13)
        +gridColumn()
          = i + 1

  section#grid-container
    h2.font_size--large-xx Container
    p the grids or any other element can be nested inside a `.grid_container` class
    p the widths of the container per breakpoint:
    ol.list
      li.list-item mobile_s: 100%
      li.list-item mobile_m: 100%
      li.list-item mobile_l: 100%
      li.list-item tablet: 736px
      li.list-item laptop: 992px
      li.list-item laptop_l: 1120px
      li.list-item laptop_4k: 1120px
    .demo_grid
      .grid_container .grid_container

  section#grid-row-modifiers
    h2.font_size--large-xx Rows modifiers
    p To change the default behavior of the row you can add class modifiers

    h3.font_size--large-x Columns line break
    p to prevent the row to break to next line, you can use the modifier `no_break` in the `grid_row`
    p to reset to the default, in nested rows, use the class `has_break`
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({break: false})
        each _, i in Array(13)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1

    h3.font_size--large-x Margin between rows
    p to remove the space/margin bottom between colunsadd the class `no_margin` in the `grid_row`
    p to reset to the default, in nested rows, use the class `has_margin`
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({margin: false})
        each _, i in Array(12)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1
      +gridRow()
        each _, i in Array(12)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1

    h3.font_size--large-x Vertical align columns
    p top
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignVertical: 'top', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1
    p center
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignVertical: 'center', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1
    p bottom
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignVertical: 'bottom', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1

    h3.font_size--large-x Horizontal align columns
    p left
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignHorizontal: 'left', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1
    p center
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignHorizontal: 'center', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1
    p right
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignHorizontal: 'right', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1
    p center_spaced
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignHorizontal: 'center_spaced', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1
    p center_justify
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({alignHorizontal: 'center_justify', additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        each _, i in Array(2)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1

    h3.font_size--large-x Columns directions
    p to change the default colum directoion from horizantal to vertical / stacked the class `direction_column` in the `grid_row`
    p to reset to the default, in nested rows, use the class `direction_row`
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({direction: 'column'})
        each _, i in Array(3)
          +gridColumn()
            = i + 1

  section#grid-columns-modifiers
    h2.font_size--large-xx Columns modifiers
    p To change the default behavior of the columns you can add class modifiers

    h3.font_size--large-x Column size
    p to change the column size add a class `is_NUMBER` to the column
    .demo_grid
      each _, rowCount in Array(12)
        +gridRow()
          +gridColumn({size: (rowCount + 1)})
            = (rowCount + 1)

    h3.font_size--large-x Column offset
    p to add the column offset add a class `has_offset_NUMBER` to the column
    .demo_grid
      each _, rowCount in Array(12)
        +gridRow()
          +gridColumn({offset: (rowCount + 1)})
            = (rowCount + 1)

    h3.font_size--large-x Column order
    p to change the column order add a class `is_order_NUMBER` to the column
    p the default order is 1, so they will folow the order in HTML if no `is_order_NUMBER` is present
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow()
        +gridColumn({order: 3 })
          | 1 HTML
        +gridColumn({order: 2 })
          | 2 HTML
        +gridColumn()
          | 3 HTML
        +gridColumn()
        | 4 HTML

    h3.font_size--large-x Vertical align column
    p stretch
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        +gridColumn()
          | 1
        +gridColumn({alignVertical: 'stretch'})
          | 2
    p top
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        +gridColumn()
          | 1
        +gridColumn({alignVertical: 'top'})
          | 2
    p center
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        +gridColumn()
          | 1
        +gridColumn({alignVertical: 'center'})
          | 2
    p bottom
    .demo_grid
      +gridRow({additionalClass: 'has_height_4'})
        +gridColumn()
          | 1
        +gridColumn({alignVertical: 'bottom'})
          | 2




